  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "As of now, Facebook does not provide a feature that allows users to see who has viewed their profiles. Any third-party app or service claiming to offer this capability is likely misleading or a potential security risk. Facebook emphasizes user privacy and does not share viewing statistics for individual profiles with users.\n\nIf you are concerned about your privacy or any suspicious activity on your account, review your privacy settings and consider enhancing your security measures by enabling two-factor authentication or regularly updating your password.",
